                <h1>William James: Pioneering Psychology and Functionalism</h1>
                <p>William James, a foundational figure in psychology, emphasized the importance of pragmatic approaches to understanding the human mind. He introduced functionalism, focusing on mental processes as adaptive functions. His work explored consciousness, habit, and emotion, influencing both psychology and philosophy, and reflecting the interplay between mind and behavior.</p>
